sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant KServeRouter as KServe Router<br/>(Ingress/Route)
    participant VLLMPod as vllm-rocm Pod<br/>8000/TCP HTTP<br/>8033/TCP gRPC
    participant GPU as AMD ROCm GPU<br/>PCIe/ROCm
    participant S3 as Model Storage<br/>(S3/PVC)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant HF as Hugging Face Hub<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over VLLMPod,S3: Flow 3: Model Loading at Startup
    VLLMPod->>S3: Download model weights<br/>HTTPS/443 or Filesystem<br/>Auth: IAM / ServiceAccount
    S3-->>VLLMPod: Model artifacts
    VLLMPod->>GPU: Load model into GPU memory<br/>PCIe/ROCm
    opt Model not pre-cached
        VLLMPod->>HF: Download weights/tokenizer<br/>HTTPS/443<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (optional)
        HF-->>VLLMPod: Model files
    end

    Note over Client,GPU: Flow 1: OpenAI-Compatible HTTP Inference
    Client->>KServeRouter: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>Auth: Platform-level (KServe)
    KServeRouter->>VLLMPod: Forward request<br/>HTTP/8000<br/>Plaintext (pod-level)
    VLLMPod->>GPU: Inference computation<br/>PCIe/ROCm
    GPU-->>VLLMPod: Generated tokens
    VLLMPod-->>KServeRouter: JSON Response<br/>HTTP/8000
    KServeRouter-->>Client: Inference result

    Note over Client,GPU: Flow 2: TGIS gRPC Inference
    Client->>KServeRouter: GenerationService RPC<br/>Auth: Platform-level (KServe)
    KServeRouter->>VLLMPod: Forward request<br/>gRPC/8033<br/>Plaintext (pod-level)
    VLLMPod->>GPU: Inference computation<br/>PCIe/ROCm
    GPU-->>VLLMPod: Generated tokens
    VLLMPod-->>KServeRouter: gRPC Response<br/>gRPC/8033
    KServeRouter-->>Client: Inference result
